  "texts": [
    "This is the standard statistical approach when it comes to comparing distributions of ordinal data.",
    "foot_11 Consider two samples of equal size, giving distributions P and Q over the same n available answer levels.",
    "We set an uniform cost to moving one observation from one level to the previous or next level.",
    "EMD is defined as the total cost of the less costly solution that transforms P into Q by moving observations along the levels.",
    "It is then divided by the theoretical maximum (n -1), so that the resulting normalized measure ranges between 0 and 1."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}